item.description:
The new zebra crossing which crosses the A40 at this location has the wrong colour tactile paving slabs installed - they should be red, for a controlled crossing (as opposed to yellow for an uncontrolled crossing). From Gov Guidance: &quot;Controlled crossings are those where motorised vehicles and cycles must stop at a red light or give way, so pedestrians have priority in law. For the purposes of this guidance, controlled crossings consist of give-way crossings and signal-controlled crossings, as listed below. Give-way crossings: • Zebra crossings, where drivers must give way to any pedestrian on the crossing. At controlled crossings the blister surface should be red (the colour that has been established for this application since 1981) to indicate to partially sighted people that the crossing is controlled. Red blister paving should not be used in any other circumstances.&quot;
